annotationA: Niemann-Pick type protein homolog 1B; Important for cholesterol absorption at the midgut epithelium. Acts only in the early steps of sterol absorption, prior to Npc1a-dependent intracellular sterol trafficking
annotationB: Protein NPC2 homolog; Functions redundantly with Npc2b in regulating sterol homeostasis and ecdysteroid biosynthesis, probably by controlling the availability of sterol substrate
